oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Bleak House, ca. 1895
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: unknown
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Bleak House, Kingston Pike, Knoxville, TN, ca. 1895. The house was built as a wedding gift for Robert Houston Armstrong and Louisa Franklin. The house is also known as Confederate Memorial Hall.
